    "body": "### Problem\n\nNo matter how long the prompt is, mark `:` is always in column 2 (1-based index). This means it is neither in the start of the prompt nor the start of user input\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:set buftype=prompt\n:startinsert | stopinsert\n:echo col(\"':\") \" => 2\n\n:vsplit | edit foo\n:set buftype=prompt\n:call bufnr(\"%\")->prompt_setprompt(\"Hello prompt\")\n:startinsert | stopinsert\n:echo col(\"':\") \" => 2\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI don't know what is the intended behavior of this mark, but it should either be in the start column of the prompt (which is 1 (1-based index)), or start column of user input\n\nPing @shadmansaleh \n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-484f455\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNA\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNA\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNA\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nNA\n\n### Installation\n\nsource",
